        "description": "* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive\nrainfall is expected.\n\n* WHERE...A portion of central Alabama, including the following\ncounties, Blount, Calhoun, Jefferson, St. Clair and Talladega.\n\n* WHEN...Until 1115 PM CDT.\n\n* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 807 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to\nthunderstorms. This will cause urban and small stream\nflooding.\n- Some locations that will experience flooding include...\nBirmingham, Mountain Brook, Trussville, Gardendale, Pell\nCity, Irondale, Leeds, Moody, Fairfield, Fultondale,\nSpringville, Odenville, Center Point, Pleasant Grove, Clay,\nPinson, Tarrant, Lincoln, Adamsville and Margaret.",
